# Identity is intentionally NOT set globally — must be set explicitly per repo.
# This avoids accidentally committing under the wrong identity (e.g. work vs. personal).
#
# To set identity for a single repo (run inside the repo):
#   git config user.name "John Paulsen"
#   git config user.email "john@gopaulsen.com"
#
# Or use conditional includes for per-directory identity. Example:
#   [includeIf "gitdir:~/work/"]
#     path = ~/.gitconfig-work
#   [includeIf "gitdir:~/personal/"]
#     path = ~/.gitconfig-personal
# See: https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config#_conditional_includes
